article.headline: Ball State 69, Central Michigan 56
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. (AP) -- Terrance Chapman scored 15 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead Ball State past Central Michigan 69-56 Thursday night. The game was tied 30-30 at halftime but the Cardinals (12-6, 7-3 Mid-American) went on a 9-0 run to start the second half and never looked back on the way to their third straight win and seventh in nine games. Central Michigan (7-12, 2-9) -- which shot 13 percent for a half in a loss to Western Michigan last week -- shot just 33 percent in the second half, while the Cardinals hit 54 percent of their shots. Dennis Trammell led Ball State with 16 points while Peyton Stovall added 13 and Julien Mills chipped in 10. Giordan Watson led the Chippewas with 21 points while Tom Pantlind had a career-high 13 points and snagged eight rebounds.
